description:
&lt;p&gt;SAU ward has a vacancy for a deputy manager as a band 6.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Surgical Assessment Unit is responsible for the urgent assessment of specialities including Colorectal, Hepatobiliary &amp; Oesophageal-Gastric, Vascular &amp; Urology Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a large ambulatory triage area, 2 examination rooms and an ultrasound suite &amp; 22 inpatient beds situated within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The existing band 6 team is made up of 5 individuals who are expected to provide triage clinical expertise, leadership and management skills on a daily basis. Opportunity for training will be provided however acute surgical ward experience and triaging would be an advantage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information regarding this role and to arrange an informal walk around please contact Sister Andrews on sianandrews@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
